## Why classes are THE practical-screen skill

Multi-level assessments (CodeSignal's industry format included) are almost always "build a system": a storage service, a banking ledger, an inventory. One class, state in dicts, methods added level by level. You need to write this shape without thinking:

```python
class CloudStorage:
    def __init__(self):
        self.files = {}            # name -> size
        self.users = {}            # user -> capacity info

    def add_file(self, name, size):
        if name in self.files:
            return False
        self.files[name] = size
        return True

    def get_file_size(self, name):
        return self.files.get(name)   # None if missing
```

